5094
5095bool Parser::isConstructorDeclarator(bool IsUnqualified, bool DeductionGuide) {
5096 TentativeParsingAction TPA(*this);
5097
5098 // Parse the C++ scope specifier.
5099 CXXScopeSpec SS;
5100 if (ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, nullptr,
5101 /*EnteringContext=*/true)) {
5102 TPA.Revert();
5103 return false;
5104 }
5105
5106 // Parse the constructor name.
5107 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
5108 // We already know that we have a constructor name; just consume
5109 // the token.
5110 ConsumeToken();
5111 } else if (Tok.is(tok::annot_template_id)) {
5112 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
5113 } else {
5114 TPA.Revert();
5115 return false;
5116 }
5117
5118 // There may be attributes here, appertaining to the constructor name or type
5119 // we just stepped past.
5120 SkipCXX11Attributes();
5121
5122 // Current class name must be followed by a left parenthesis.
5123 if (Tok.isNot(tok::l_paren)) {
5124 TPA.Revert();
5125 return false;
5126 }
5127 ConsumeParen();
5128
5129 // A right parenthesis, or ellipsis followed by a right parenthesis signals
5130 // that we have a constructor.
5131 if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren) ||
5132 (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) && NextToken().is(tok::r_paren))) {
5133 TPA.Revert();
5134 return true;
5135 }
5136
5137 // A C++11 attribute here signals that we have a constructor, and is an
5138 // attribute on the first constructor parameter.
5139 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
5140 isCXX11AttributeSpecifier(/*Disambiguate*/ false,
5141 /*OuterMightBeMessageSend*/ true)) {
5142 TPA.Revert();
5143 return true;
5144 }
5145
5146 // If we need to, enter the specified scope.
5147 DeclaratorScopeObj DeclScopeObj(*this, SS);
5148 if (SS.isSet() && Actions.ShouldEnterDeclaratorScope(getCurScope(), SS))
5149 DeclScopeObj.EnterDeclaratorScope();
5150
5151 // Optionally skip Microsoft attributes.
5152 ParsedAttributes Attrs(AttrFactory);
5153 MaybeParseMicrosoftAttributes(Attrs);
5154
5155 // Check whether the next token(s) are part of a declaration
5156 // specifier, in which case we have the start of a parameter and,
5157 // therefore, we know that this is a constructor.
5158 bool IsConstructor = false;
5159 if (isDeclarationSpecifier())
5160 IsConstructor = true;
5161 else if (Tok.is(tok::identifier) ||
5162 (Tok.is(tok::annot_cxxscope) && NextToken().is(tok::identifier))) {
5163 // We've seen "C ( X" or "C ( X::Y", but "X" / "X::Y" is not a type.
5164 // This might be a parenthesized member name, but is more likely to
5165 // be a constructor declaration with an invalid argument type. Keep
5166 // looking.
5167 if (Tok.is(tok::annot_cxxscope))
5168 ConsumeAnnotationToken();
5169 ConsumeToken();
5170
5171 // If this is not a constructor, we must be parsing a declarator,
5172 // which must have one of the following syntactic forms (see the
5173 // grammar extract at the start of ParseDirectDeclarator):
5174 switch (Tok.getKind()) {
5175 case tok::l_paren:
5176 // C(X ( int));
5177 case tok::l_square:
5178 // C(X [ 5]);
5179 // C(X [ [attribute]]);
5180 case tok::coloncolon:
5181 // C(X :: Y);
5182 // C(X :: *p);
5183 // Assume this isn't a constructor, rather than assuming it's a
5184 // constructor with an unnamed parameter of an ill-formed type.
5185 break;
5186
5187 case tok::r_paren:
5188 // C(X )
5189
5190 // Skip past the right-paren and any following attributes to get to
5191 // the function body or trailing-return-type.
5192 ConsumeParen();
5193 SkipCXX11Attributes();
5194
5195 if (DeductionGuide) {
5196 // C(X) -> ... is a deduction guide.
5197 IsConstructor = Tok.is(tok::arrow);
5198 break;
5199 }
5200 if (Tok.is(tok::colon) || Tok.is(tok::kw_try)) {
5201 // Assume these were meant to be constructors:
5202 // C(X) : (the name of a bit-field cannot be parenthesized).
5203 // C(X) try (this is otherwise ill-formed).
5204 IsConstructor = true;
5205 }
5206 if (Tok.is(tok::semi) || Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
5207 // If we have a constructor name within the class definition,
5208 // assume these were meant to be constructors:
5209 // C(X) {
5210 // C(X) ;
5211 // ... because otherwise we would be declaring a non-static data
5212 // member that is ill-formed because it's of the same type as its
5213 // surrounding class.
5214 //
5215 // FIXME: We can actually do this whether or not the name is qualified,
5216 // because if it is qualified in this context it must be being used as
5217 // a constructor name.
5218 // currently, so we're somewhat conservative here.
5219 IsConstructor = IsUnqualified;
5220 }
5221 break;
5222
5223 default:
5224 IsConstructor = true;
5225 break;
5226 }
5227 }
5228
5229 TPA.Revert();
5230 return IsConstructor;
5231}
5232
5233/// ParseTypeQualifierListOpt
5234/// type-qualifier-list: [C99 6.7.5]
5235/// type-qualifier
5236/// [vendor] attributes
5237/// [ only if AttrReqs & AR_VendorAttributesParsed ]
5238/// type-qualifier-list type-qualifier
5239/// [vendor] type-qualifier-list attributes
5240/// [ only if AttrReqs & AR_VendorAttributesParsed ]
5241/// [C++0x] attribute-specifier[opt] is allowed before cv-qualifier-seq
5242/// [ only if AttReqs & AR_CXX11AttributesParsed ]
5243/// Note: vendor can be GNU, MS, etc and can be explicitly controlled via
5244/// AttrRequirements bitmask values.
5245void Parser::ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(
5246 DeclSpec &DS, unsigned AttrReqs, bool AtomicAllowed,
5247 bool IdentifierRequired,
5248 Optional<llvm::function_ref<void()>> CodeCompletionHandler) {
5249 if (standardAttributesAllowed() && (AttrReqs & AR_CXX11AttributesParsed) &&
5250 isCXX11AttributeSpecifier()) {
5251 ParsedAttributesWithRange attrs(AttrFactory);
5252 ParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
5253 DS.takeAttributesFrom(attrs);
5254 }
5255
5256 SourceLocation EndLoc;
5257
5258 while (1) {
5259 bool isInvalid = false;
5260 const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
5261 unsigned DiagID = 0;
5262 SourceLocation Loc = Tok.getLocation();
5263
5264 switch (Tok.getKind()) {
5265 case tok::code_completion:
5266 if (CodeCompletionHandler)
5267 (*CodeCompletionHandler)();
5268 else
5269 Actions.CodeCompleteTypeQualifiers(DS);
5270 return cutOffParsing();
5271
5272 case tok::kw_const:
5273 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_const , Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
5274 getLangOpts());
5275 break;
5276 case tok::kw_volatile:
5277 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_volatile, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
5278 getLangOpts());
5279 break;
5280 case tok::kw_restrict:
5281 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_restrict, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
5282 getLangOpts());
5283 break;
5284 case tok::kw__Atomic:
5285 if (!AtomicAllowed)
5286 goto DoneWithTypeQuals;
5287 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_atomic, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
5288 getLangOpts());
5289 break;
5290 case tok::kw___input:
5291 isInvalid = DS.SetInput(PrevSpec, DiagID);
5292 break;
5293 case tok::kw___output:
5294 isInvalid = DS.SetOutput(PrevSpec, DiagID);
5295 break;
5296
5297 // OpenCL qualifiers:
5298 case tok::kw_private:
5299 if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL)
5300 goto DoneWithTypeQuals;
5301 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5302 case tok::kw___private:
5303 case tok::kw___global:
5304 case tok::kw___local:
5305 case tok::kw___constant:
5306 case tok::kw___generic:
5307 case tok::kw___read_only:
5308 case tok::kw___write_only:
5309 case tok::kw___read_write:
5310 ParseOpenCLQualifiers(DS.getAttributes());
5311 break;
5312
5313 case tok::kw___unaligned:
5314 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeQual(DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,
5315 getLangOpts());
5316 break;
5317 case tok::kw___uptr:
5318 // GNU libc headers in C mode use '__uptr' as an identifier which conflicts
5319 // with the MS modifier keyword.
5320 if ((AttrReqs & AR_DeclspecAttributesParsed) && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5321 IdentifierRequired && DS.isEmpty() && NextToken().is(tok::semi)) {
5322 if (TryKeywordIdentFallback(false))
5323 continue;
5324 }
5325 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5326 case tok::kw___sptr:
5327 case tok::kw___w64:
5328 case tok::kw___ptr64:
5329 case tok::kw___ptr32:
5330 case tok::kw___cdecl:
5331 case tok::kw___stdcall:
5332 case tok::kw___fastcall:
5333 case tok::kw___thiscall:
5334 case tok::kw___regcall:
5335 case tok::kw___vectorcall:
5336 if (AttrReqs & AR_DeclspecAttributesParsed) {
5337 ParseMicrosoftTypeAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
5338 continue;
5339 }
5340 goto DoneWithTypeQuals;
5341 case tok::kw___pascal:
5342 if (AttrReqs & AR_VendorAttributesParsed) {
5343 ParseBorlandTypeAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
5344 continue;
5345 }
5346 goto DoneWithTypeQuals;
5347
5348 // Nullability type specifiers.
5349 case tok::kw__Nonnull:
5350 case tok::kw__Nullable:
5351 case tok::kw__Null_unspecified:
5352 ParseNullabilityTypeSpecifiers(DS.getAttributes());
5353 continue;
5354
5355 // Objective-C 'kindof' types.
5356 case tok::kw___kindof:
5357 DS.getAttributes().addNew(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Loc, nullptr, Loc,
5358 nullptr, 0, ParsedAttr::AS_Keyword);
5359 (void)ConsumeToken();
5360 continue;
5361
5362 case tok::kw___attribute:
5363 if (AttrReqs & AR_GNUAttributesParsedAndRejected)
5364 // When GNU attributes are expressly forbidden, diagnose their usage.
5365 Diag(Tok, diag::err_attributes_not_allowed);
5366
5367 // Parse the attributes even if they are rejected to ensure that error
5368 // recovery is graceful.
5369 if (AttrReqs & AR_GNUAttributesParsed ||
5370 AttrReqs & AR_GNUAttributesParsedAndRejected) {
5371 ParseGNUAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
5372 continue; // do *not* consume the next token!
5373 }
5374 // otherwise, FALL THROUGH!
5375 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
5376 default:
5377 DoneWithTypeQuals:
5378 // If this is not a type-qualifier token, we're done reading type
5379 // qualifiers. First verify that DeclSpec's are consistent.
5380 DS.Finish(Actions, Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
5381 if (EndLoc.isValid())
5382 DS.SetRangeEnd(EndLoc);
5383 return;
5384 }
5385
5386 // If the specifier combination wasn't legal, issue a diagnostic.
5387 if (isInvalid) {
5388 assert(PrevSpec && "Method did not return previous specifier!");
5389 Diag(Tok, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
5390 }
5391 EndLoc = ConsumeToken();
5392 }
5393}
5394
5395/// ParseDeclarator - Parse and verify a newly-initialized declarator.
5396///
5397void Parser::ParseDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
5398 /// This implements the 'declarator' production in the C grammar, then checks
5399 /// for well-formedness and issues diagnostics.
5400 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, &Parser::ParseDirectDeclarator);
5401}
5402
5403static bool isPtrOperatorToken(tok::TokenKind Kind, const LangOptions &Lang,
5404 DeclaratorContext TheContext) {
5405 if (Kind == tok::star || Kind == tok::caret)
5406 return true;
5407
5408 if (Kind == tok::kw_pipe &&
5409 ((Lang.OpenCL && Lang.OpenCLVersion >= 200) || Lang.OpenCLCPlusPlus))
5410 return true;
5411
5412 if (!Lang.CPlusPlus)
5413 return false;
5414
5415 if (Kind == tok::amp)
5416 return true;
5417
5418 // We parse rvalue refs in C++03, because otherwise the errors are scary.
5419 // But we must not parse them in conversion-type-ids and new-type-ids, since
5420 // those can be legitimately followed by a && operator.
5421 // (The same thing can in theory happen after a trailing-return-type, but
5422 // since those are a C++11 feature, there is no rejects-valid issue there.)
5423 if (Kind == tok::ampamp)
5424 return Lang.CPlusPlus11 ||
5425 (TheContext != DeclaratorContext::ConversionIdContext &&
5426 TheContext != DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext);
5427
5428 return false;
5429}
5430
5431// Indicates whether the given declarator is a pipe declarator.
5432static bool isPipeDeclerator(const Declarator &D) {
5433 const unsigned NumTypes = D.getNumTypeObjects();
5434
5435 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx != NumTypes; ++Idx)
5436 if (DeclaratorChunk::Pipe == D.getTypeObject(Idx).Kind)
5437 return true;
5438
5439 return false;
5440}
5441
5442/// ParseDeclaratorInternal - Parse a C or C++ declarator. The direct-declarator
5443/// is parsed by the function passed to it. Pass null, and the direct-declarator
5444/// isn't parsed at all, making this function effectively parse the C++
5445/// ptr-operator production.
5446///
5447/// If the grammar of this construct is extended, matching changes must also be
5448/// made to TryParseDeclarator and MightBeDeclarator, and possibly to
5449/// isConstructorDeclarator.
5450///
5451/// declarator: [C99 6.7.5] [C++ 8p4, dcl.decl]
5452/// [C] pointer[opt] direct-declarator
5453/// [C++] direct-declarator
5454/// [C++] ptr-operator declarator
5455///
5456/// pointer: [C99 6.7.5]
5457/// '*' type-qualifier-list[opt]
5458/// '*' type-qualifier-list[opt] pointer
5459///
5460/// ptr-operator:
5461/// '*' cv-qualifier-seq[opt]
5462/// '&'
5463/// [C++0x] '&&'
5464/// [GNU] '&' restrict[opt] attributes[opt]
5465/// [GNU?] '&&' restrict[opt] attributes[opt]
5466/// '::'[opt] nested-name-specifier '*' cv-qualifier-seq[opt]
5467void Parser::ParseDeclaratorInternal(Declarator &D,
5468 DirectDeclParseFunction DirectDeclParser) {
5469 if (Diags.hasAllExtensionsSilenced())
5470 D.setExtension();
5471
5472 // C++ member pointers start with a '::' or a nested-name.
5473 // Member pointers get special handling, since there's no place for the
5474 // scope spec in the generic path below.
5475 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5476 (Tok.is(tok::coloncolon) || Tok.is(tok::kw_decltype) ||
5477 (Tok.is(tok::identifier) &&
5478 (NextToken().is(tok::coloncolon) || NextToken().is(tok::less))) ||
5479 Tok.is(tok::annot_cxxscope))) {
5480 bool EnteringContext =
5481 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::FileContext ||
5482 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext;
5483 CXXScopeSpec SS;
5484 ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(SS, nullptr, EnteringContext);
5485
5486 if (SS.isNotEmpty()) {
5487 if (Tok.isNot(tok::star)) {
5488 // The scope spec really belongs to the direct-declarator.
5489 if (D.mayHaveIdentifier())
5490 D.getCXXScopeSpec() = SS;
5491 else
5492 AnnotateScopeToken(SS, true);
5493
5494 if (DirectDeclParser)
5495 (this->*DirectDeclParser)(D);
5496 return;
5497 }
5498
5499 SourceLocation Loc = ConsumeToken();
5500 D.SetRangeEnd(Loc);
5501 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
5502 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS);
5503 D.ExtendWithDeclSpec(DS);
5504
5505 // Recurse to parse whatever is left.
5506 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, DirectDeclParser);
5507
5508 // Sema will have to catch (syntactically invalid) pointers into global
5509 // scope. It has to catch pointers into namespace scope anyway.
5510 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getMemberPointer(
5511 SS, DS.getTypeQualifiers(), DS.getEndLoc()),
5512 std::move(DS.getAttributes()),
5513 /* Don't replace range end. */ SourceLocation());
5514 return;
5515 }
5516 }
5517
5518 tok::TokenKind Kind = Tok.getKind();
5519
5520 if (D.getDeclSpec().isTypeSpecPipe() && !isPipeDeclerator(D)) {
5521 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
5522 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS);
5523
5524 D.AddTypeInfo(
5525 DeclaratorChunk::getPipe(DS.getTypeQualifiers(), DS.getPipeLoc()),
5526 std::move(DS.getAttributes()), SourceLocation());
5527 }
5528
5529 // Not a pointer, C++ reference, or block.
5530 if (!isPtrOperatorToken(Kind, getLangOpts(), D.getContext())) {
5531 if (DirectDeclParser)
5532 (this->*DirectDeclParser)(D);
5533 return;
5534 }
5535
5536 // Otherwise, '*' -> pointer, '^' -> block, '&' -> lvalue reference,
5537 // '&&' -> rvalue reference
5538 SourceLocation Loc = ConsumeToken(); // Eat the *, ^, & or &&.
5539 D.SetRangeEnd(Loc);
5540
5541 if (Kind == tok::star || Kind == tok::caret) {
5542 // Is a pointer.
5543 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
5544
5545 // GNU attributes are not allowed here in a new-type-id, but Declspec and
5546 // C++11 attributes are allowed.
5547 unsigned Reqs = AR_CXX11AttributesParsed | AR_DeclspecAttributesParsed |
5548 ((D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::CXXNewContext)
5549 ? AR_GNUAttributesParsed
5550 : AR_GNUAttributesParsedAndRejected);
5551 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS, Reqs, true, !D.mayOmitIdentifier());
5552 D.ExtendWithDeclSpec(DS);
5553
5554 // Recursively parse the declarator.
5555 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, DirectDeclParser);
5556 if (Kind == tok::star)
5557 // Remember that we parsed a pointer type, and remember the type-quals.
5558 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getPointer(
5559 DS.getTypeQualifiers(), Loc, DS.getConstSpecLoc(),
5560 DS.getVolatileSpecLoc(), DS.getRestrictSpecLoc(),
5561 DS.getAtomicSpecLoc(), DS.getUnalignedSpecLoc()),
5562 std::move(DS.getAttributes()), SourceLocation());
5563 else
5564 // Remember that we parsed a Block type, and remember the type-quals.
5565 D.AddTypeInfo(
5566 DeclaratorChunk::getBlockPointer(DS.getTypeQualifiers(), Loc),
5567 std::move(DS.getAttributes()), SourceLocation());
5568 } else {
5569 // Is a reference
5570 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
5571
5572 // Complain about rvalue references in C++03, but then go on and build
5573 // the declarator.
5574 if (Kind == tok::ampamp)
5575 Diag(Loc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
5576 diag::warn_cxx98_compat_rvalue_reference :
5577 diag::ext_rvalue_reference);
5578
5579 // GNU-style and C++11 attributes are allowed here, as is restrict.
5580 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS);
5581 D.ExtendWithDeclSpec(DS);
5582
5583 // C++ 8.3.2p1: cv-qualified references are ill-formed except when the
5584 // cv-qualifiers are introduced through the use of a typedef or of a
5585 // template type argument, in which case the cv-qualifiers are ignored.
5586 if (DS.getTypeQualifiers() != DeclSpec::TQ_unspecified) {
5587 if (DS.getTypeQualifiers() & DeclSpec::TQ_const)
5588 Diag(DS.getConstSpecLoc(),
5589 diag::err_invalid_reference_qualifier_application) << "const";
5590 if (DS.getTypeQualifiers() & DeclSpec::TQ_volatile)
5591 Diag(DS.getVolatileSpecLoc(),
5592 diag::err_invalid_reference_qualifier_application) << "volatile";
5593 // 'restrict' is permitted as an extension.
5594 if (DS.getTypeQualifiers() & DeclSpec::TQ_atomic)
5595 Diag(DS.getAtomicSpecLoc(),
5596 diag::err_invalid_reference_qualifier_application) << "_Atomic";
5597 }
5598
5599 // Recursively parse the declarator.
5600 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, DirectDeclParser);
5601
5602 if (D.getNumTypeObjects() > 0) {
5603 // C++ [dcl.ref]p4: There shall be no references to references.
5604 DeclaratorChunk& InnerChunk = D.getTypeObject(D.getNumTypeObjects() - 1);
5605 if (InnerChunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference) {
5606 if (const IdentifierInfo *II = D.getIdentifier())
5607 Diag(InnerChunk.Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_reference_to_reference)
5608 << II;
5609 else
5610 Diag(InnerChunk.Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_reference_to_reference)
5611 << "type name";
5612
5613 // Once we've complained about the reference-to-reference, we
5614 // can go ahead and build the (technically ill-formed)
5615 // declarator: reference collapsing will take care of it.
5616 }
5617 }
5618
5619 // Remember that we parsed a reference type.
5620 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getReference(DS.getTypeQualifiers(), Loc,
5621 Kind == tok::amp),
5622 std::move(DS.getAttributes()), SourceLocation());
5623 }
5624}
5625
5626// When correcting from misplaced brackets before the identifier, the location
5627// is saved inside the declarator so that other diagnostic messages can use
5628// them. This extracts and returns that location, or returns the provided
5629// location if a stored location does not exist.
5630static SourceLocation getMissingDeclaratorIdLoc(Declarator &D,
5631 SourceLocation Loc) {
5632 if (D.getName().StartLocation.isInvalid() &&
5633 D.getName().EndLocation.isValid())
5634 return D.getName().EndLocation;
5635
5636 return Loc;
5637}
5638
5639/// ParseDirectDeclarator
5640/// direct-declarator: [C99 6.7.5]
5641/// [C99] identifier
5642/// '(' declarator ')'
5643/// [GNU] '(' attributes declarator ')'
5644/// [C90] direct-declarator '[' constant-expression[opt] ']'
5645/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list[opt] assignment-expr[opt] ']'
5646/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' 'static' type-qual-list[opt] assign-expr ']'
5647/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list 'static' assignment-expr ']'
5648/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list[opt] '*' ']'
5649/// [C++11] direct-declarator '[' constant-expression[opt] ']'
5650/// attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
5651/// direct-declarator '(' parameter-type-list ')'
5652/// direct-declarator '(' identifier-list[opt] ')'
5653/// [GNU] direct-declarator '(' parameter-forward-declarations
5654/// parameter-type-list[opt] ')'
5655/// [C++] direct-declarator '(' parameter-declaration-clause ')'
5656/// cv-qualifier-seq[opt] exception-specification[opt]
5657/// [C++11] direct-declarator '(' parameter-declaration-clause ')'
5658/// attribute-specifier-seq[opt] cv-qualifier-seq[opt]
5659/// ref-qualifier[opt] exception-specification[opt]
5660/// [C++] declarator-id
5661/// [C++11] declarator-id attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
5662///
5663/// declarator-id: [C++ 8]
5664/// '...'[opt] id-expression
5665/// '::'[opt] nested-name-specifier[opt] type-name
5666///
5667/// id-expression: [C++ 5.1]
5668/// unqualified-id
5669/// qualified-id
5670///
5671/// unqualified-id: [C++ 5.1]
5672/// identifier
5673/// operator-function-id
5674/// conversion-function-id
5675/// '~' class-name
5676/// template-id
5677///
5678/// C++17 adds the following, which we also handle here:
5679///
5680/// simple-declaration:
5681/// <decl-spec> '[' identifier-list ']' brace-or-equal-initializer ';'
5682///
5683/// Note, any additional constructs added here may need corresponding changes
5684/// in isConstructorDeclarator.
5685void Parser::ParseDirectDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
5686 DeclaratorScopeObj DeclScopeObj(*this, D.getCXXScopeSpec());
5687
5688 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D.mayHaveIdentifier()) {
5689 // This might be a C++17 structured binding.
5690 if (Tok.is(tok::l_square) && !D.mayOmitIdentifier() &&
5691 D.getCXXScopeSpec().isEmpty())
5692 return ParseDecompositionDeclarator(D);
5693
5694 // Don't parse FOO:BAR as if it were a typo for FOO::BAR inside a class, in
5695 // this context it is a bitfield. Also in range-based for statement colon
5696 // may delimit for-range-declaration.
5697 ColonProtectionRAIIObject X(
5698 *this, D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext ||
5699 (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::ForContext &&
5700 getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11));
5701
5702 // ParseDeclaratorInternal might already have parsed the scope.
5703 if (D.getCXXScopeSpec().isEmpty()) {
5704 bool EnteringContext =
5705 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::FileContext ||
5706 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext;
5707 ParseOptionalCXXScopeSpecifier(D.getCXXScopeSpec(), nullptr,
5708 EnteringContext);
5709 }
5710
5711 if (D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid()) {
5712 if (Actions.ShouldEnterDeclaratorScope(getCurScope(),
5713 D.getCXXScopeSpec()))
5714 // Change the declaration context for name lookup, until this function
5715 // is exited (and the declarator has been parsed).
5716 DeclScopeObj.EnterDeclaratorScope();
5717 else if (getObjCDeclContext()) {
5718 // Ensure that we don't interpret the next token as an identifier when
5719 // dealing with declarations in an Objective-C container.
5720 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5721 D.setInvalidType(true);
5722 ConsumeToken();
5723 goto PastIdentifier;
5724 }
5725 }
5726
5727 // C++0x [dcl.fct]p14:
5728 // There is a syntactic ambiguity when an ellipsis occurs at the end of a
5729 // parameter-declaration-clause without a preceding comma. In this case,
5730 // the ellipsis is parsed as part of the abstract-declarator if the type
5731 // of the parameter either names a template parameter pack that has not
5732 // been expanded or contains auto; otherwise, it is parsed as part of the
5733 // parameter-declaration-clause.
5734 if (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) && D.getCXXScopeSpec().isEmpty() &&
5735 !((D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext ||
5736 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext ||
5737 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteralContext) &&
5738 NextToken().is(tok::r_paren) &&
5739 !D.hasGroupingParens() &&
5740 !Actions.containsUnexpandedParameterPacks(D) &&
5741 D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecType() != TST_auto)) {
5742 SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = ConsumeToken();
5743 if (isPtrOperatorToken(Tok.getKind(), getLangOpts(), D.getContext())) {
5744 // The ellipsis was put in the wrong place. Recover, and explain to
5745 // the user what they should have done.
5746 ParseDeclarator(D);
5747 if (EllipsisLoc.isValid())
5748 DiagnoseMisplacedEllipsisInDeclarator(EllipsisLoc, D);
5749 return;
5750 } else
5751 D.setEllipsisLoc(EllipsisLoc);
5752
5753 // The ellipsis can't be followed by a parenthesized declarator. We
5754 // check for that in ParseParenDeclarator, after we have disambiguated
5755 // the l_paren token.
5756 }
5757
5758 if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::identifier, tok::kw_operator, tok::annot_template_id,
5759 tok::tilde)) {
5760 // We found something that indicates the start of an unqualified-id.
5761 // Parse that unqualified-id.
5762 bool AllowConstructorName;
5763 bool AllowDeductionGuide;
5764 if (D.getDeclSpec().hasTypeSpecifier()) {
5765 AllowConstructorName = false;
5766 AllowDeductionGuide = false;
5767 } else if (D.getCXXScopeSpec().isSet()) {
5768 AllowConstructorName =
5769 (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::FileContext ||
5770 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext);
5771 AllowDeductionGuide = false;
5772 } else {
5773 AllowConstructorName =
5774 (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext);
5775 AllowDeductionGuide =
5776 (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::FileContext ||
5777 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext);
5778 }
5779
5780 bool HadScope = D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid();
5781 if (ParseUnqualifiedId(D.getCXXScopeSpec(),
5782 /*EnteringContext=*/true,
5783 /*AllowDestructorName=*/true, AllowConstructorName,
5784 AllowDeductionGuide, nullptr, nullptr,
5785 D.getName()) ||
5786 // Once we're past the identifier, if the scope was bad, mark the
5787 // whole declarator bad.
5788 D.getCXXScopeSpec().isInvalid()) {
5789 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5790 D.setInvalidType(true);
5791 } else {
5792 // ParseUnqualifiedId might have parsed a scope specifier during error
5793 // recovery. If it did so, enter that scope.
5794 if (!HadScope && D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid() &&
5795 Actions.ShouldEnterDeclaratorScope(getCurScope(),
5796 D.getCXXScopeSpec()))
5797 DeclScopeObj.EnterDeclaratorScope();
5798
5799 // Parsed the unqualified-id; update range information and move along.
5800 if (D.getSourceRange().getBegin().isInvalid())
5801 D.SetRangeBegin(D.getName().getSourceRange().getBegin());
5802 D.SetRangeEnd(D.getName().getSourceRange().getEnd());
5803 }
5804 goto PastIdentifier;
5805 }
5806
5807 if (D.getCXXScopeSpec().isNotEmpty()) {
5808 // We have a scope specifier but no following unqualified-id.
5809 Diag(PP.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getCXXScopeSpec().getEndLoc()),
5810 diag::err_expected_unqualified_id)
5811 << /*C++*/1;
5812 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5813 goto PastIdentifier;
5814 }
5815 } else if (Tok.is(tok::identifier) && D.mayHaveIdentifier()) {
5816 assert(!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5817 "There's a C++-specific check for tok::identifier above");
5818 assert(Tok.getIdentifierInfo() && "Not an identifier?");
5819 D.SetIdentifier(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Tok.getLocation());
5820 D.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getLocation());
5821 ConsumeToken();
5822 goto PastIdentifier;
5823 } else if (Tok.is(tok::identifier) && !D.mayHaveIdentifier()) {
5824 // We're not allowed an identifier here, but we got one. Try to figure out
5825 // if the user was trying to attach a name to the type, or whether the name
5826 // is some unrelated trailing syntax.
5827 bool DiagnoseIdentifier = false;
5828 if (D.hasGroupingParens())
5829 // An identifier within parens is unlikely to be intended to be anything
5830 // other than a name being "declared".
5831 DiagnoseIdentifier = true;
5832 else if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::TemplateArgContext)
5833 // T<int N> is an accidental identifier; T<int N indicates a missing '>'.
5834 DiagnoseIdentifier =
5835 NextToken().isOneOf(tok::comma, tok::greater, tok::greatergreater);
5836 else if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasDeclContext ||
5837 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplateContext)
5838 // The most likely error is that the ';' was forgotten.
5839 DiagnoseIdentifier = NextToken().isOneOf(tok::comma, tok::semi);
5840 else if ((D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnContext ||
5841 D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVarContext) &&
5842 !isCXX11VirtSpecifier(Tok))
5843 DiagnoseIdentifier = NextToken().isOneOf(
5844 tok::comma, tok::semi, tok::equal, tok::l_brace, tok::kw_try);
5845 if (DiagnoseIdentifier) {
5846 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::err_unexpected_unqualified_id)
5847 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Tok.getLocation());
5848 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5849 ConsumeToken();
5850 goto PastIdentifier;
5851 }
5852 }
5853
5854 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
5855 // If this might be an abstract-declarator followed by a direct-initializer,
5856 // check whether this is a valid declarator chunk. If it can't be, assume
5857 // that it's an initializer instead.
5858 if (D.mayOmitIdentifier() && D.mayBeFollowedByCXXDirectInit()) {
5859 RevertingTentativeParsingAction PA(*this);
5860 if (TryParseDeclarator(true, D.mayHaveIdentifier(), true) ==
5861 TPResult::False) {
5862 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5863 goto PastIdentifier;
5864 }
5865 }
5866
5867 // direct-declarator: '(' declarator ')'
5868 // direct-declarator: '(' attributes declarator ')'
5869 // Example: 'char (*X)' or 'int (*XX)(void)'
5870 ParseParenDeclarator(D);
5871
5872 // If the declarator was parenthesized, we entered the declarator
5873 // scope when parsing the parenthesized declarator, then exited
5874 // the scope already. Re-enter the scope, if we need to.
5875 if (D.getCXXScopeSpec().isSet()) {
5876 // If there was an error parsing parenthesized declarator, declarator
5877 // scope may have been entered before. Don't do it again.
5878 if (!D.isInvalidType() &&
5879 Actions.ShouldEnterDeclaratorScope(getCurScope(),
5880 D.getCXXScopeSpec()))
5881 // Change the declaration context for name lookup, until this function
5882 // is exited (and the declarator has been parsed).
5883 DeclScopeObj.EnterDeclaratorScope();
5884 }
5885 } else if (D.mayOmitIdentifier()) {
5886 // This could be something simple like "int" (in which case the declarator
5887 // portion is empty), if an abstract-declarator is allowed.
5888 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5889
5890 // The grammar for abstract-pack-declarator does not allow grouping parens.
5891 // FIXME: Revisit this once core issue 1488 is resolved.
5892 if (D.hasEllipsis() && D.hasGroupingParens())
5893 Diag(PP.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getEllipsisLoc()),
5894 diag::ext_abstract_pack_declarator_parens);
5895 } else {
5896 if (Tok.getKind() == tok::annot_pragma_parser_crash)
5897 LLVM_BUILTIN_TRAP;
5898 if (Tok.is(tok::l_square))
5899 return ParseMisplacedBracketDeclarator(D);
5900 if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext) {
5901 // Objective-C++: Detect C++ keywords and try to prevent further errors by
5902 // treating these keyword as valid member names.
5903 if (getLangOpts().ObjC && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5904 Tok.getIdentifierInfo() &&
5905 Tok.getIdentifierInfo()->isCPlusPlusKeyword(getLangOpts())) {
5906 Diag(getMissingDeclaratorIdLoc(D, Tok.getLocation()),
5907 diag::err_expected_member_name_or_semi_objcxx_keyword)
5908 << Tok.getIdentifierInfo()
5909 << (D.getDeclSpec().isEmpty() ? SourceRange()
5910 : D.getDeclSpec().getSourceRange());
5911 D.SetIdentifier(Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Tok.getLocation());
5912 D.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getLocation());
5913 ConsumeToken();
5914 goto PastIdentifier;
5915 }
5916 Diag(getMissingDeclaratorIdLoc(D, Tok.getLocation()),
5917 diag::err_expected_member_name_or_semi)
5918 << (D.getDeclSpec().isEmpty() ? SourceRange()
5919 : D.getDeclSpec().getSourceRange());
5920 } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5921 if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::period, tok::arrow))
5922 Diag(Tok, diag::err_invalid_operator_on_type) << Tok.is(tok::arrow);
5923 else {
5924 SourceLocation Loc = D.getCXXScopeSpec().getEndLoc();
5925 if (Tok.isAtStartOfLine() && Loc.isValid())
5926 Diag(PP.getLocForEndOfToken(Loc), diag::err_expected_unqualified_id)
5927 << getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
5928 else
5929 Diag(getMissingDeclaratorIdLoc(D, Tok.getLocation()),
5930 diag::err_expected_unqualified_id)
5931 << getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
5932 }
5933 } else {
5934 Diag(getMissingDeclaratorIdLoc(D, Tok.getLocation()),
5935 diag::err_expected_either)
5936 << tok::identifier << tok::l_paren;
5937 }
5938 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
5939 D.setInvalidType(true);
5940 }
5941
5942 PastIdentifier:
5943 assert(D.isPastIdentifier() &&
5944 "Haven't past the location of the identifier yet?");
5945
5946 // Don't parse attributes unless we have parsed an unparenthesized name.
5947 if (D.hasName() && !D.getNumTypeObjects())
5948 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(D);
5949
5950 while (1) {
5951 if (Tok.is(tok::l_paren)) {
5952 // Enter function-declaration scope, limiting any declarators to the
5953 // function prototype scope, including parameter declarators.
5954 ParseScope PrototypeScope(this,
5955 Scope::FunctionPrototypeScope|Scope::DeclScope|
5956 (D.isFunctionDeclaratorAFunctionDeclaration()
5957 ? Scope::FunctionDeclarationScope : 0));
5958
5959 // The paren may be part of a C++ direct initializer, eg. "int x(1);".
5960 // In such a case, check if we actually have a function declarator; if it
5961 // is not, the declarator has been fully parsed.
5962 bool IsAmbiguous = false;
5963 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D.mayBeFollowedByCXXDirectInit()) {
5964 // The name of the declarator, if any, is tentatively declared within
5965 // a possible direct initializer.
5966 TentativelyDeclaredIdentifiers.push_back(D.getIdentifier());
5967 bool IsFunctionDecl = isCXXFunctionDeclarator(&IsAmbiguous);
5968 TentativelyDeclaredIdentifiers.pop_back();
5969 if (!IsFunctionDecl)
5970 break;
5971 }
5972 ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
5973 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
5974 T.consumeOpen();
5975 ParseFunctionDeclarator(D, attrs, T, IsAmbiguous);
5976 PrototypeScope.Exit();
5977 } else if (Tok.is(tok::l_square)) {
5978 ParseBracketDeclarator(D);
5979 } else {
5980 break;
5981 }
5982 }
5983}
5984
5985void Parser::ParseDecompositionDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
5986 assert(Tok.is(tok::l_square));
5987
5988 // If this doesn't look like a structured binding, maybe it's a misplaced
5989 // array declarator.
5990 // FIXME: Consume the l_square first so we don't need extra lookahead for
5991 // this.
5992 if (!(NextToken().is(tok::identifier) &&
5993 GetLookAheadToken(2).isOneOf(tok::comma, tok::r_square)) &&
5994 !(NextToken().is(tok::r_square) &&
5995 GetLookAheadToken(2).isOneOf(tok::equal, tok::l_brace)))
5996 return ParseMisplacedBracketDeclarator(D);
5997
5998 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_square);
5999 T.consumeOpen();
6000
6001 SmallVector<DecompositionDeclarator::Binding, 32> Bindings;
6002 while (Tok.isNot(tok::r_square)) {
6003 if (!Bindings.empty()) {
6004 if (Tok.is(tok::comma))
6005 ConsumeToken();
6006 else {
6007 if (Tok.is(tok::identifier)) {
6008 SourceLocation EndLoc = getEndOfPreviousToken();
6009 Diag(EndLoc, diag::err_expected)
6010 << tok::comma << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EndLoc, ",");
6011 } else {
6012 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected_comma_or_rsquare);
6013 }
6014
6015 SkipUntil(tok::r_square, tok::comma, tok::identifier,
6016 StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
6017 if (Tok.is(tok::comma))
6018 ConsumeToken();
6019 else if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier))
6020 break;
6021 }
6022 }
6023
6024 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
6025 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
6026 break;
6027 }
6028
6029 Bindings.push_back({Tok.getIdentifierInfo(), Tok.getLocation()});
6030 ConsumeToken();
6031 }
6032
6033 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_square))
6034 // We've already diagnosed a problem here.
6035 T.skipToEnd();
6036 else {
6037 // C++17 does not allow the identifier-list in a structured binding
6038 // to be empty.
6039 if (Bindings.empty())
6040 Diag(Tok.getLocation(), diag::ext_decomp_decl_empty);
6041
6042 T.consumeClose();
6043 }
6044
6045 return D.setDecompositionBindings(T.getOpenLocation(), Bindings,
6046 T.getCloseLocation());
6047}
6048
6049/// ParseParenDeclarator - We parsed the declarator D up to a paren. This is
6050/// only called before the identifier, so these are most likely just grouping
6051/// parens for precedence. If we find that these are actually function
6052/// parameter parens in an abstract-declarator, we call ParseFunctionDeclarator.
6053///
6054/// direct-declarator:
6055/// '(' declarator ')'
6056/// [GNU] '(' attributes declarator ')'
6057/// direct-declarator '(' parameter-type-list ')'
6058/// direct-declarator '(' identifier-list[opt] ')'
6059/// [GNU] direct-declarator '(' parameter-forward-declarations
6060/// parameter-type-list[opt] ')'
6061///
6062void Parser::ParseParenDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
6063 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
6064 T.consumeOpen();
6065
6066 assert(!D.isPastIdentifier() && "Should be called before passing identifier");
6067
6068 // Eat any attributes before we look at whether this is a grouping or function
6069 // declarator paren. If this is a grouping paren, the attribute applies to
6070 // the type being built up, for example:
6071 // int (__attribute__(()) *x)(long y)
6072 // If this ends up not being a grouping paren, the attribute applies to the
6073 // first argument, for example:
6074 // int (__attribute__(()) int x)
6075 // In either case, we need to eat any attributes to be able to determine what
6076 // sort of paren this is.
6077 //
6078 ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
6079 bool RequiresArg = false;
6080 if (Tok.is(tok::kw___attribute)) {
6081 ParseGNUAttributes(attrs);
6082
6083 // We require that the argument list (if this is a non-grouping paren) be
6084 // present even if the attribute list was empty.
6085 RequiresArg = true;
6086 }
6087
6088 // Eat any Microsoft extensions.
6089 ParseMicrosoftTypeAttributes(attrs);
6090
6091 // Eat any Borland extensions.
6092 if (Tok.is(tok::kw___pascal))
6093 ParseBorlandTypeAttributes(attrs);
6094
6095 // If we haven't past the identifier yet (or where the identifier would be
6096 // stored, if this is an abstract declarator), then this is probably just
6097 // grouping parens. However, if this could be an abstract-declarator, then
6098 // this could also be the start of function arguments (consider 'void()').
6099 bool isGrouping;
6100
6101 if (!D.mayOmitIdentifier()) {
6102 // If this can't be an abstract-declarator, this *must* be a grouping
6103 // paren, because we haven't seen the identifier yet.
6104 isGrouping = true;
6105 } else if (Tok.is(tok::r_paren) || // 'int()' is a function.
6106 (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) &&
6107 NextToken().is(tok::r_paren)) || // C++ int(...)
6108 isDeclarationSpecifier() || // 'int(int)' is a function.
6109 isCXX11AttributeSpecifier()) { // 'int([[]]int)' is a function.
6110 // This handles C99 6.7.5.3p11: in "typedef int X; void foo(X)", X is
6111 // considered to be a type, not a K&R identifier-list.
6112 isGrouping = false;
6113 } else {
6114 // Otherwise, this is a grouping paren, e.g. 'int (*X)' or 'int(X)'.
6115 isGrouping = true;
6116 }
6117
6118 // If this is a grouping paren, handle:
6119 // direct-declarator: '(' declarator ')'
6120 // direct-declarator: '(' attributes declarator ')'
6121 if (isGrouping) {
6122 SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = D.getEllipsisLoc();
6123 D.setEllipsisLoc(SourceLocation());
6124
6125 bool hadGroupingParens = D.hasGroupingParens();
6126 D.setGroupingParens(true);
6127 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, &Parser::ParseDirectDeclarator);
6128 // Match the ')'.
6129 T.consumeClose();
6130 D.AddTypeInfo(
6131 DeclaratorChunk::getParen(T.getOpenLocation(), T.getCloseLocation()),
6132 std::move(attrs), T.getCloseLocation());
6133
6134 D.setGroupingParens(hadGroupingParens);
6135
6136 // An ellipsis cannot be placed outside parentheses.
6137 if (EllipsisLoc.isValid())
6138 DiagnoseMisplacedEllipsisInDeclarator(EllipsisLoc, D);
6139
6140 return;
6141 }
6142
6143 // Okay, if this wasn't a grouping paren, it must be the start of a function
6144 // argument list. Recognize that this declarator will never have an
6145 // identifier (and remember where it would have been), then call into
6146 // ParseFunctionDeclarator to handle of argument list.
6147 D.SetIdentifier(nullptr, Tok.getLocation());
6148
6149 // Enter function-declaration scope, limiting any declarators to the
6150 // function prototype scope, including parameter declarators.
6151 ParseScope PrototypeScope(this,
6152 Scope::FunctionPrototypeScope | Scope::DeclScope |
6153 (D.isFunctionDeclaratorAFunctionDeclaration()
6154 ? Scope::FunctionDeclarationScope : 0));
6155 ParseFunctionDeclarator(D, attrs, T, false, RequiresArg);
6156 PrototypeScope.Exit();
6157}
6158
6159/// ParseFunctionDeclarator - We are after the identifier and have parsed the
6160/// declarator D up to a paren, which indicates that we are parsing function
6161/// arguments.
6162///
6163/// If FirstArgAttrs is non-null, then the caller parsed those arguments
6164/// immediately after the open paren - they should be considered to be the
6165/// first argument of a parameter.
6166///
6167/// If RequiresArg is true, then the first argument of the function is required
6168/// to be present and required to not be an identifier list.
6169///
6170/// For C++, after the parameter-list, it also parses the cv-qualifier-seq[opt],
6171/// (C++11) ref-qualifier[opt], exception-specification[opt],
6172/// (C++11) attribute-specifier-seq[opt], and (C++11) trailing-return-type[opt].
6173///
6174/// [C++11] exception-specification:
6175/// dynamic-exception-specification
6176/// noexcept-specification
6177///
6178void Parser::ParseFunctionDeclarator(Declarator &D,
6179 ParsedAttributes &FirstArgAttrs,
6180 BalancedDelimiterTracker &Tracker,
6181 bool IsAmbiguous,
6182 bool RequiresArg) {
6183 assert(getCurScope()->isFunctionPrototypeScope() &&
6184 "Should call from a Function scope");
6185 // lparen is already consumed!
6186 assert(D.isPastIdentifier() && "Should not call before identifier!");
6187
6188 // This should be true when the function has typed arguments.
6189 // Otherwise, it is treated as a K&R-style function.
6190 bool HasProto = false;
6191 // Build up an array of information about the parsed arguments.
6192 SmallVector<DeclaratorChunk::ParamInfo, 16> ParamInfo;
6193 // Remember where we see an ellipsis, if any.
6194 SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
6195
6196 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
6197 bool RefQualifierIsLValueRef = true;
6198 SourceLocation RefQualifierLoc;
6199 ExceptionSpecificationType ESpecType = EST_None;
6200 SourceRange ESpecRange;
6201 SmallVector<ParsedType, 2> DynamicExceptions;
6202 SmallVector<SourceRange, 2> DynamicExceptionRanges;
6203 ExprResult NoexceptExpr;
6204 CachedTokens *ExceptionSpecTokens = nullptr;
6205 ParsedAttributesWithRange FnAttrs(AttrFactory);
6206 TypeResult TrailingReturnType;
6207
6208 /* LocalEndLoc is the end location for the local FunctionTypeLoc.
6209 EndLoc is the end location for the function declarator.
6210 They differ for trailing return types. */
6211 SourceLocation StartLoc, LocalEndLoc, EndLoc;
6212 SourceLocation LParenLoc, RParenLoc;
6213 LParenLoc = Tracker.getOpenLocation();
6214 StartLoc = LParenLoc;
6215
6216 if (isFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList()) {
6217 if (RequiresArg)
6218 Diag(Tok, diag::err_argument_required_after_attribute);
6219
6220 ParseFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList(D, ParamInfo);
6221
6222 Tracker.consumeClose();
6223 RParenLoc = Tracker.getCloseLocation();
6224 LocalEndLoc = RParenLoc;
6225 EndLoc = RParenLoc;
6226
6227 // If there are attributes following the identifier list, parse them and
6228 // prohibit them.
6229 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(FnAttrs);
6230 ProhibitAttributes(FnAttrs);
6231 } else {
6232 if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_paren))
6233 ParseParameterDeclarationClause(D, FirstArgAttrs, ParamInfo,
6234 EllipsisLoc);
6235 else if (RequiresArg)
6236 Diag(Tok, diag::err_argument_required_after_attribute);
6237
6238 HasProto = ParamInfo.size() || getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
6239 || getLangOpts().OpenCL;
6240
6241 // If we have the closing ')', eat it.
6242 Tracker.consumeClose();
6243 RParenLoc = Tracker.getCloseLocation();
6244 LocalEndLoc = RParenLoc;
6245 EndLoc = RParenLoc;
6246
6247 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6248 // FIXME: Accept these components in any order, and produce fixits to
6249 // correct the order if the user gets it wrong. Ideally we should deal
6250 // with the pure-specifier in the same way.
6251
6252 // Parse cv-qualifier-seq[opt].
6253 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS, AR_NoAttributesParsed,
6254 /*AtomicAllowed*/ false,
6255 /*IdentifierRequired=*/false,
6256 llvm::function_ref<void()>([&]() {
6257 Actions.CodeCompleteFunctionQualifiers(DS, D);
6258 }));
6259 if (!DS.getSourceRange().getEnd().isInvalid()) {
6260 EndLoc = DS.getSourceRange().getEnd();
6261 }
6262
6263 // Parse ref-qualifier[opt].
6264 if (ParseRefQualifier(RefQualifierIsLValueRef, RefQualifierLoc))
6265 EndLoc = RefQualifierLoc;
6266
6267 // C++11 [expr.prim.general]p3:
6268 // If a declaration declares a member function or member function
6269 // template of a class X, the expression this is a prvalue of type
6270 // "pointer to cv-qualifier-seq X" between the optional cv-qualifer-seq
6271 // and the end of the function-definition, member-declarator, or
6272 // declarator.
6273 // FIXME: currently, "static" case isn't handled correctly.
6274 bool IsCXX11MemberFunction =
6275 getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
6276 D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_typedef &&
6277 (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext
6278 ? !D.getDeclSpec().isFriendSpecified()
6279 : D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::FileContext &&
6280 D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid() &&
6281 Actions.CurContext->isRecord());
6282
6283 Qualifiers Q = Qualifiers::fromCVRUMask(DS.getTypeQualifiers());
6284 if (D.getDeclSpec().isConstexprSpecified() && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14)
6285 Q.addConst();
6286 // FIXME: Collect C++ address spaces.
6287 // If there are multiple different address spaces, the source is invalid.
6288 // Carry on using the first addr space for the qualifiers of 'this'.
6289 // The diagnostic will be given later while creating the function
6290 // prototype for the method.
6291 if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus) {
6292 for (ParsedAttr &attr : DS.getAttributes()) {
6293 LangAS ASIdx = attr.asOpenCLLangAS();
6294 if (ASIdx != LangAS::Default) {
6295 Q.addAddressSpace(ASIdx);
6296 break;
6297 }
6298 }
6299 }
6300
6301 Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(
6302 Actions, dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Actions.CurContext), Q,
6303 IsCXX11MemberFunction);
6304
6305 // Parse exception-specification[opt].
6306 bool Delayed = D.isFirstDeclarationOfMember() &&
6307 D.isFunctionDeclaratorAFunctionDeclaration();
6308 if (Delayed && Actions.isLibstdcxxEagerExceptionSpecHack(D) &&
6309 GetLookAheadToken(0).is(tok::kw_noexcept) &&
6310 GetLookAheadToken(1).is(tok::l_paren) &&
6311 GetLookAheadToken(2).is(tok::kw_noexcept) &&
6312 GetLookAheadToken(3).is(tok::l_paren) &&
6313 GetLookAheadToken(4).is(tok::identifier) &&
6314 GetLookAheadToken(4).getIdentifierInfo()->isStr("swap")) {
6315 // HACK: We've got an exception-specification
6316 // noexcept(noexcept(swap(...)))
6317 // or
6318 // noexcept(noexcept(swap(...)) && noexcept(swap(...)))
6319 // on a 'swap' member function. This is a libstdc++ bug; the lookup
6320 // for 'swap' will only find the function we're currently declaring,
6321 // whereas it expects to find a non-member swap through ADL. Turn off
6322 // delayed parsing to give it a chance to find what it expects.
6323 Delayed = false;
6324 }
6325 ESpecType = tryParseExceptionSpecification(Delayed,
6326 ESpecRange,
6327 DynamicExceptions,
6328 DynamicExceptionRanges,
6329 NoexceptExpr,
6330 ExceptionSpecTokens);
6331 if (ESpecType != EST_None)
6332 EndLoc = ESpecRange.getEnd();
6333
6334 // Parse attribute-specifier-seq[opt]. Per DR 979 and DR 1297, this goes
6335 // after the exception-specification.
6336 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(FnAttrs);
6337
6338 // Parse trailing-return-type[opt].
6339 LocalEndLoc = EndLoc;
6340 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Tok.is(tok::arrow)) {
6341 Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_trailing_return_type);
6342 if (D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecType() == TST_auto)
6343 StartLoc = D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc();
6344 LocalEndLoc = Tok.getLocation();
6345 SourceRange Range;
6346 TrailingReturnType =
6347 ParseTrailingReturnType(Range, D.mayBeFollowedByCXXDirectInit());
6348 EndLoc = Range.getEnd();
6349 }
6350 } else if (standardAttributesAllowed()) {
6351 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(FnAttrs);
6352 }
6353 }
6354
6355 // Collect non-parameter declarations from the prototype if this is a function
6356 // declaration. They will be moved into the scope of the function. Only do
6357 // this in C and not C++, where the decls will continue to live in the
6358 // surrounding context.
6359 SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 0> DeclsInPrototype;
6360 if (getCurScope()->getFlags() & Scope::FunctionDeclarationScope &&
6361 !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6362 for (Decl *D : getCurScope()->decls()) {
6363 NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D);
6364 if (!ND || isa<ParmVarDecl>(ND))
6365 continue;
6366 DeclsInPrototype.push_back(ND);
6367 }
6368 }
6369
6370 // Remember that we parsed a function type, and remember the attributes.
6371 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getFunction(
6372 HasProto, IsAmbiguous, LParenLoc, ParamInfo.data(),
6373 ParamInfo.size(), EllipsisLoc, RParenLoc,
6374 RefQualifierIsLValueRef, RefQualifierLoc,
6375 /*MutableLoc=*/SourceLocation(),
6376 ESpecType, ESpecRange, DynamicExceptions.data(),
6377 DynamicExceptionRanges.data(), DynamicExceptions.size(),
6378 NoexceptExpr.isUsable() ? NoexceptExpr.get() : nullptr,
6379 ExceptionSpecTokens, DeclsInPrototype, StartLoc,
6380 LocalEndLoc, D, TrailingReturnType, &DS),
6381 std::move(FnAttrs), EndLoc);
6382}
6383
6384/// ParseRefQualifier - Parses a member function ref-qualifier. Returns
6385/// true if a ref-qualifier is found.
6386bool Parser::ParseRefQualifier(bool &RefQualifierIsLValueRef,
6387 SourceLocation &RefQualifierLoc) {
6388 if (Tok.isOneOf(tok::amp, tok::ampamp)) {
6389 Diag(Tok, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
6390 diag::warn_cxx98_compat_ref_qualifier :
6391 diag::ext_ref_qualifier);
6392
6393 RefQualifierIsLValueRef = Tok.is(tok::amp);
6394 RefQualifierLoc = ConsumeToken();
6395 return true;
6396 }
6397 return false;
6398}
6399
6400/// isFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList - This parameter list may have an
6401/// identifier list form for a K&R-style function: void foo(a,b,c)
6402///
6403/// Note that identifier-lists are only allowed for normal declarators, not for
6404/// abstract-declarators.
6405bool Parser::isFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList() {
6406 return !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
6407 && Tok.is(tok::identifier)
6408 && !TryAltiVecVectorToken()
6409 // K&R identifier lists can't have typedefs as identifiers, per C99
6410 // 6.7.5.3p11.
6411 && (TryAnnotateTypeOrScopeToken() || !Tok.is(tok::annot_typename))
6412 // Identifier lists follow a really simple grammar: the identifiers can
6413 // be followed *only* by a ", identifier" or ")". However, K&R
6414 // identifier lists are really rare in the brave new modern world, and
6415 // it is very common for someone to typo a type in a non-K&R style
6416 // list. If we are presented with something like: "void foo(intptr x,
6417 // float y)", we don't want to start parsing the function declarator as
6418 // though it is a K&R style declarator just because intptr is an
6419 // invalid type.
6420 //
6421 // To handle this, we check to see if the token after the first
6422 // identifier is a "," or ")". Only then do we parse it as an
6423 // identifier list.
6424 && (!Tok.is(tok::eof) &&
6425 (NextToken().is(tok::comma) || NextToken().is(tok::r_paren)));
6426}
6427
6428/// ParseFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList - While parsing a function declarator
6429/// we found a K&R-style identifier list instead of a typed parameter list.
6430///
6431/// After returning, ParamInfo will hold the parsed parameters.
6432///
6433/// identifier-list: [C99 6.7.5]
6434/// identifier
6435/// identifier-list ',' identifier
6436///
6437void Parser::ParseFunctionDeclaratorIdentifierList(
6438 Declarator &D,
6439 SmallVectorImpl<DeclaratorChunk::ParamInfo> &ParamInfo) {
6440 // If there was no identifier specified for the declarator, either we are in
6441 // an abstract-declarator, or we are in a parameter declarator which was found
6442 // to be abstract. In abstract-declarators, identifier lists are not valid:
6443 // diagnose this.
6444 if (!D.getIdentifier())
6445 Diag(Tok, diag::ext_ident_list_in_param);
6446
6447 // Maintain an efficient lookup of params we have seen so far.
6448 llvm::SmallSet<const IdentifierInfo*, 16> ParamsSoFar;
6449
6450 do {
6451 // If this isn't an identifier, report the error and skip until ')'.
6452 if (Tok.isNot(tok::identifier)) {
6453 Diag(Tok, diag::err_expected) << tok::identifier;
6454 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
6455 // Forget we parsed anything.
6456 ParamInfo.clear();
6457 return;
6458 }
6459
6460 IdentifierInfo *ParmII = Tok.getIdentifierInfo();
6461
6462 // Reject 'typedef int y; int test(x, y)', but continue parsing.
6463 if (Actions.getTypeName(*ParmII, Tok.getLocation(), getCurScope()))
6464 Diag(Tok, diag::err_unexpected_typedef_ident) << ParmII;
6465
6466 // Verify that the argument identifier has not already been mentioned.
6467 if (!ParamsSoFar.insert(ParmII).second) {
6468 Diag(Tok, diag::err_param_redefinition) << ParmII;
6469 } else {
6470 // Remember this identifier in ParamInfo.
6471 ParamInfo.push_back(DeclaratorChunk::ParamInfo(ParmII,
6472 Tok.getLocation(),
6473 nullptr));
6474 }
6475
6476 // Eat the identifier.
6477 ConsumeToken();
6478 // The list continues if we see a comma.
6479 } while (TryConsumeToken(tok::comma));
6480}
6481
6482/// ParseParameterDeclarationClause - Parse a (possibly empty) parameter-list
6483/// after the opening parenthesis. This function will not parse a K&R-style
6484/// identifier list.
6485///
6486/// D is the declarator being parsed. If FirstArgAttrs is non-null, then the
6487/// caller parsed those arguments immediately after the open paren - they should
6488/// be considered to be part of the first parameter.
6489///
6490/// After returning, ParamInfo will hold the parsed parameters. EllipsisLoc will
6491/// be the location of the ellipsis, if any was parsed.
6492///
6493/// parameter-type-list: [C99 6.7.5]
6494/// parameter-list
6495/// parameter-list ',' '...'
6496/// [C++] parameter-list '...'
6497///
6498/// parameter-list: [C99 6.7.5]
6499/// parameter-declaration
6500/// parameter-list ',' parameter-declaration
6501///
6502/// parameter-declaration: [C99 6.7.5]
6503/// declaration-specifiers declarator
6504/// [C++] declaration-specifiers declarator '=' assignment-expression
6505/// [C++11] initializer-clause
6506/// [GNU] declaration-specifiers declarator attributes
6507/// declaration-specifiers abstract-declarator[opt]
6508/// [C++] declaration-specifiers abstract-declarator[opt]
6509/// '=' assignment-expression
6510/// [GNU] declaration-specifiers abstract-declarator[opt] attributes
6511/// [C++11] attribute-specifier-seq parameter-declaration
6512///
6513void Parser::ParseParameterDeclarationClause(
6514 Declarator &D,
6515 ParsedAttributes &FirstArgAttrs,
6516 SmallVectorImpl<DeclaratorChunk::ParamInfo> &ParamInfo,
6517 SourceLocation &EllipsisLoc) {
6518 do {
6519 // FIXME: Issue a diagnostic if we parsed an attribute-specifier-seq
6520 // before deciding this was a parameter-declaration-clause.
6521 if (TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc))
6522 break;
6523
6524 // Parse the declaration-specifiers.
6525 // Just use the ParsingDeclaration "scope" of the declarator.
6526 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
6527
6528 // Parse any C++11 attributes.
6529 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(DS.getAttributes());
6530
6531 // Skip any Microsoft attributes before a param.
6532 MaybeParseMicrosoftAttributes(DS.getAttributes());
6533
6534 SourceLocation DSStart = Tok.getLocation();
6535
6536 // If the caller parsed attributes for the first argument, add them now.
6537 // Take them so that we only apply the attributes to the first parameter.
6538 // FIXME: If we can leave the attributes in the token stream somehow, we can
6539 // get rid of a parameter (FirstArgAttrs) and this statement. It might be
6540 // too much hassle.
6541 DS.takeAttributesFrom(FirstArgAttrs);
6542
6543 ParseDeclarationSpecifiers(DS);
6544
6545
6546 // Parse the declarator. This is "PrototypeContext" or
6547 // "LambdaExprParameterContext", because we must accept either
6548 // 'declarator' or 'abstract-declarator' here.
6549 Declarator ParmDeclarator(
6550 DS, D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprContext
6551 ? DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameterContext
6552 : DeclaratorContext::PrototypeContext);
6553 ParseDeclarator(ParmDeclarator);
6554
6555 // Parse GNU attributes, if present.
6556 MaybeParseGNUAttributes(ParmDeclarator);
6557
6558 // Remember this parsed parameter in ParamInfo.
6559 IdentifierInfo *ParmII = ParmDeclarator.getIdentifier();
6560
6561 // DefArgToks is used when the parsing of default arguments needs
6562 // to be delayed.
6563 std::unique_ptr<CachedTokens> DefArgToks;
6564
6565 // If no parameter was specified, verify that *something* was specified,
6566 // otherwise we have a missing type and identifier.
6567 if (DS.isEmpty() && ParmDeclarator.getIdentifier() == nullptr &&
6568 ParmDeclarator.getNumTypeObjects() == 0) {
6569 // Completely missing, emit error.
6570 Diag(DSStart, diag::err_missing_param);
6571 } else {
6572 // Otherwise, we have something. Add it and let semantic analysis try
6573 // to grok it and add the result to the ParamInfo we are building.
6574
6575 // Last chance to recover from a misplaced ellipsis in an attempted
6576 // parameter pack declaration.
6577 if (Tok.is(tok::ellipsis) &&
6578 (NextToken().isNot(tok::r_paren) ||
6579 (!ParmDeclarator.getEllipsisLoc().isValid() &&
6580 !Actions.isUnexpandedParameterPackPermitted())) &&
6581 Actions.containsUnexpandedParameterPacks(ParmDeclarator))
6582 DiagnoseMisplacedEllipsisInDeclarator(ConsumeToken(), ParmDeclarator);
6583
6584 // Inform the actions module about the parameter declarator, so it gets
6585 // added to the current scope.
6586 Decl *Param = Actions.ActOnParamDeclarator(getCurScope(), ParmDeclarator);
6587 // Parse the default argument, if any. We parse the default
6588 // arguments in all dialects; the semantic analysis in
6589 // ActOnParamDefaultArgument will reject the default argument in
6590 // C.
6591 if (Tok.is(tok::equal)) {
6592 SourceLocation EqualLoc = Tok.getLocation();
6593
6594 // Parse the default argument
6595 if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::MemberContext) {
6596 // If we're inside a class definition, cache the tokens
6597 // corresponding to the default argument. We'll actually parse
6598 // them when we see the end of the class definition.
6599 DefArgToks.reset(new CachedTokens);
6600
6601 SourceLocation ArgStartLoc = NextToken().getLocation();
6602 if (!ConsumeAndStoreInitializer(*DefArgToks, CIK_DefaultArgument)) {
6603 DefArgToks.reset();
6604 Actions.ActOnParamDefaultArgumentError(Param, EqualLoc);
6605 } else {
6606 Actions.ActOnParamUnparsedDefaultArgument(Param, EqualLoc,
6607 ArgStartLoc);
6608 }
6609 } else {
6610 // Consume the '='.
6611 ConsumeToken();
6612
6613 // The argument isn't actually potentially evaluated unless it is
6614 // used.
6615 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Eval(
6616 Actions,
6617 Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluatedIfUsed,
6618 Param);
6619
6620 ExprResult DefArgResult;
6621 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && Tok.is(tok::l_brace)) {
6622 Diag(Tok, diag::warn_cxx98_compat_generalized_initializer_lists);
6623 DefArgResult = ParseBraceInitializer();
6624 } else
6625 DefArgResult = ParseAssignmentExpression();
6626 DefArgResult = Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(DefArgResult);
6627 if (DefArgResult.isInvalid()) {
6628 Actions.ActOnParamDefaultArgumentError(Param, EqualLoc);
6629 SkipUntil(tok::comma, tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi | StopBeforeMatch);
6630 } else {
6631 // Inform the actions module about the default argument
6632 Actions.ActOnParamDefaultArgument(Param, EqualLoc,
6633 DefArgResult.get());
6634 }
6635 }
6636 }
6637
6638 ParamInfo.push_back(DeclaratorChunk::ParamInfo(ParmII,
6639 ParmDeclarator.getIdentifierLoc(),
6640 Param, std::move(DefArgToks)));
6641 }
6642
6643 if (TryConsumeToken(tok::ellipsis, EllipsisLoc)) {
6644 if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6645 // We have ellipsis without a preceding ',', which is ill-formed
6646 // in C. Complain and provide the fix.
6647 Diag(EllipsisLoc, diag::err_missing_comma_before_ellipsis)
6648 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EllipsisLoc, ", ");
6649 } else if (ParmDeclarator.getEllipsisLoc().isValid() ||
6650 Actions.containsUnexpandedParameterPacks(ParmDeclarator)) {
6651 // It looks like this was supposed to be a parameter pack. Warn and
6652 // point out where the ellipsis should have gone.
6653 SourceLocation ParmEllipsis = ParmDeclarator.getEllipsisLoc();
6654 Diag(EllipsisLoc, diag::warn_misplaced_ellipsis_vararg)
6655 << ParmEllipsis.isValid() << ParmEllipsis;
6656 if (ParmEllipsis.isValid()) {
6657 Diag(ParmEllipsis,
6658 diag::note_misplaced_ellipsis_vararg_existing_ellipsis);
6659 } else {
6660 Diag(ParmDeclarator.getIdentifierLoc(),
6661 diag::note_misplaced_ellipsis_vararg_add_ellipsis)
6662 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(ParmDeclarator.getIdentifierLoc(),
6663 "...")
6664 << !ParmDeclarator.hasName();
6665 }
6666 Diag(EllipsisLoc, diag::note_misplaced_ellipsis_vararg_add_comma)
6667 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EllipsisLoc, ", ");
6668 }
6669
6670 // We can't have any more parameters after an ellipsis.
6671 break;
6672 }
6673
6674 // If the next token is a comma, consume it and keep reading arguments.
6675 } while (TryConsumeToken(tok::comma));
6676}
6677
6678/// [C90] direct-declarator '[' constant-expression[opt] ']'
6679/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list[opt] assignment-expr[opt] ']'
6680/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' 'static' type-qual-list[opt] assign-expr ']'
6681/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list 'static' assignment-expr ']'
6682/// [C99] direct-declarator '[' type-qual-list[opt] '*' ']'
6683/// [C++11] direct-declarator '[' constant-expression[opt] ']'
6684/// attribute-specifier-seq[opt]
6685void Parser::ParseBracketDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
6686 if (CheckProhibitedCXX11Attribute())
6687 return;
6688
6689 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_square);
6690 T.consumeOpen();
6691
6692 // C array syntax has many features, but by-far the most common is [] and [4].
6693 // This code does a fast path to handle some of the most obvious cases.
6694 if (Tok.getKind() == tok::r_square) {
6695 T.consumeClose();
6696 ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
6697 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
6698
6699 // Remember that we parsed the empty array type.
6700 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getArray(0, false, false, nullptr,
6701 T.getOpenLocation(),
6702 T.getCloseLocation()),
6703 std::move(attrs), T.getCloseLocation());
6704 return;
6705 } else if (Tok.getKind() == tok::numeric_constant &&
6706 GetLookAheadToken(1).is(tok::r_square)) {
6707 // [4] is very common. Parse the numeric constant expression.
6708 ExprResult ExprRes(Actions.ActOnNumericConstant(Tok, getCurScope()));
6709 ConsumeToken();
6710
6711 T.consumeClose();
6712 ParsedAttributes attrs(AttrFactory);
6713 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(attrs);
6714
6715 // Remember that we parsed a array type, and remember its features.
6716 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getArray(0, false, false, ExprRes.get(),
6717 T.getOpenLocation(),
6718 T.getCloseLocation()),
6719 std::move(attrs), T.getCloseLocation());
6720 return;
6721 } else if (Tok.getKind() == tok::code_completion) {
6722 Actions.CodeCompleteBracketDeclarator(getCurScope());
6723 return cutOffParsing();
6724 }
6725
6726 // If valid, this location is the position where we read the 'static' keyword.
6727 SourceLocation StaticLoc;
6728 TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_static, StaticLoc);
6729
6730 // If there is a type-qualifier-list, read it now.
6731 // Type qualifiers in an array subscript are a C99 feature.
6732 DeclSpec DS(AttrFactory);
6733 ParseTypeQualifierListOpt(DS, AR_CXX11AttributesParsed);
6734
6735 // If we haven't already read 'static', check to see if there is one after the
6736 // type-qualifier-list.
6737 if (!StaticLoc.isValid())
6738 TryConsumeToken(tok::kw_static, StaticLoc);
6739
6740 // Handle "direct-declarator [ type-qual-list[opt] * ]".
6741 bool isStar = false;
6742 ExprResult NumElements;
6743
6744 // Handle the case where we have '[*]' as the array size. However, a leading
6745 // star could be the start of an expression, for example 'X[*p + 4]'. Verify
6746 // the token after the star is a ']'. Since stars in arrays are
6747 // infrequent, use of lookahead is not costly here.
6748 if (Tok.is(tok::star) && GetLookAheadToken(1).is(tok::r_square)) {
6749 ConsumeToken(); // Eat the '*'.
6750
6751 if (StaticLoc.isValid()) {
6752 Diag(StaticLoc, diag::err_unspecified_vla_size_with_static);
6753 StaticLoc = SourceLocation(); // Drop the static.
6754 }
6755 isStar = true;
6756 } else if (Tok.isNot(tok::r_square)) {
6757 // Note, in C89, this production uses the constant-expr production instead
6758 // of assignment-expr. The only difference is that assignment-expr allows
6759 // things like '=' and '*='. Sema rejects these in C89 mode because they
6760 // are not i-c-e's, so we don't need to distinguish between the two here.
6761
6762 // Parse the constant-expression or assignment-expression now (depending
6763 // on dialect).
6764 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6765 NumElements = ParseConstantExpression();
6766 } else {
6767 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6768 Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
6769 NumElements =
6770 Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(ParseAssignmentExpression());
6771 }
6772 } else {
6773 if (StaticLoc.isValid()) {
6774 Diag(StaticLoc, diag::err_unspecified_size_with_static);
6775 StaticLoc = SourceLocation(); // Drop the static.
6776 }
6777 }
6778
6779 // If there was an error parsing the assignment-expression, recover.
6780 if (NumElements.isInvalid()) {
6781 D.setInvalidType(true);
6782 // If the expression was invalid, skip it.
6783 SkipUntil(tok::r_square, StopAtSemi);
6784 return;
6785 }
6786
6787 T.consumeClose();
6788
6789 MaybeParseCXX11Attributes(DS.getAttributes());
6790
6791 // Remember that we parsed a array type, and remember its features.
6792 D.AddTypeInfo(
6793 DeclaratorChunk::getArray(DS.getTypeQualifiers(), StaticLoc.isValid(),
6794 isStar, NumElements.get(), T.getOpenLocation(),
6795 T.getCloseLocation()),
6796 std::move(DS.getAttributes()), T.getCloseLocation());
6797}
6798
6799/// Diagnose brackets before an identifier.
6800void Parser::ParseMisplacedBracketDeclarator(Declarator &D) {
6801 assert(Tok.is(tok::l_square) && "Missing opening bracket");
6802 assert(!D.mayOmitIdentifier() && "Declarator cannot omit identifier");
6803
6804 SourceLocation StartBracketLoc = Tok.getLocation();
6805 Declarator TempDeclarator(D.getDeclSpec(), D.getContext());
6806
6807 while (Tok.is(tok::l_square)) {
6808 ParseBracketDeclarator(TempDeclarator);
6809 }
6810
6811 // Stuff the location of the start of the brackets into the Declarator.
6812 // The diagnostics from ParseDirectDeclarator will make more sense if
6813 // they use this location instead.
6814 if (Tok.is(tok::semi))
6815 D.getName().EndLocation = StartBracketLoc;
6816
6817 SourceLocation SuggestParenLoc = Tok.getLocation();
6818
6819 // Now that the brackets are removed, try parsing the declarator again.
6820 ParseDeclaratorInternal(D, &Parser::ParseDirectDeclarator);
6821
6822 // Something went wrong parsing the brackets, in which case,
6823 // ParseBracketDeclarator has emitted an error, and we don't need to emit
6824 // one here.
6825 if (TempDeclarator.getNumTypeObjects() == 0)
6826 return;
6827
6828 // Determine if parens will need to be suggested in the diagnostic.
6829 bool NeedParens = false;
6830 if (D.getNumTypeObjects() != 0) {
6831 switch (D.getTypeObject(D.getNumTypeObjects() - 1).Kind) {
6832 case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
6833 case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
6834 case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
6835 case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
6836 case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
6837 NeedParens = true;
6838 break;
6839 case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
6840 case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
6841 case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
6842 break;
6843 }
6844 }
6845
6846 if (NeedParens) {
6847 // Create a DeclaratorChunk for the inserted parens.
6848 SourceLocation EndLoc = PP.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getEndLoc());
6849 D.AddTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getParen(SuggestParenLoc, EndLoc),
6850 SourceLocation());
6851 }
6852
6853 // Adding back the bracket info to the end of the Declarator.
6854 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TempDeclarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i < e; ++i) {
6855 const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk = TempDeclarator.getTypeObject(i);
6856 D.AddTypeInfo(Chunk, SourceLocation());
6857 }
6858
6859 // The missing identifier would have been diagnosed in ParseDirectDeclarator.
6860 // If parentheses are required, always suggest them.
6861 if (!D.getIdentifier() && !NeedParens)
6862 return;
6863
6864 SourceLocation EndBracketLoc = TempDeclarator.getEndLoc();
6865
6866 // Generate the move bracket error message.
6867 SourceRange BracketRange(StartBracketLoc, EndBracketLoc);
6868 SourceLocation EndLoc = PP.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getEndLoc());
6869
6870 if (NeedParens) {
6871 Diag(EndLoc, diag::err_brackets_go_after_unqualified_id)
6872 << getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
6873 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(SuggestParenLoc, "(")
6874 << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(EndLoc, ")")
6875 << FixItHint::CreateInsertionFromRange(
6876 EndLoc, CharSourceRange(BracketRange, true))
6877 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(BracketRange);
6878 } else {
6879 Diag(EndLoc, diag::err_brackets_go_after_unqualified_id)
6880 << getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
6881 << FixItHint::CreateInsertionFromRange(
6882 EndLoc, CharSourceRange(BracketRange, true))
6883 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(BracketRange);
6884 }
6885}
6886
6887/// [GNU] typeof-specifier:
6888/// typeof ( expressions )
6889/// typeof ( type-name )
6890/// [GNU/C++] typeof unary-expression
6891///
6892void Parser::ParseTypeofSpecifier(DeclSpec &DS) {
6893 assert(Tok.is(tok::kw_typeof) && "Not a typeof specifier");
6894 Token OpTok = Tok;
6895 SourceLocation StartLoc = ConsumeToken();
6896
6897 const bool hasParens = Tok.is(tok::l_paren);
6898
6899 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6900 Actions, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
6901 Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
6902
6903 bool isCastExpr;
6904 ParsedType CastTy;
6905 SourceRange CastRange;
6906 ExprResult Operand = Actions.CorrectDelayedTyposInExpr(
6907 ParseExprAfterUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(OpTok, isCastExpr, CastTy, CastRange));
6908 if (hasParens)
6909 DS.setTypeofParensRange(CastRange);
6910
6911 if (CastRange.getEnd().isInvalid())
6912 // FIXME: Not accurate, the range gets one token more than it should.
6913 DS.SetRangeEnd(Tok.getLocation());
6914 else
6915 DS.SetRangeEnd(CastRange.getEnd());
6916
6917 if (isCastExpr) {
6918 if (!CastTy) {
6919 DS.SetTypeSpecError();
6920 return;
6921 }
6922
6923 const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
6924 unsigned DiagID;
6925 // Check for duplicate type specifiers (e.g. "int typeof(int)").
6926 if (DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typeofType, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
6927 DiagID, CastTy,
6928 Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy()))
6929 Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
6930 return;
6931 }
6932
6933 // If we get here, the operand to the typeof was an expression.
6934 if (Operand.isInvalid()) {
6935 DS.SetTypeSpecError();
6936 return;
6937 }
6938
6939 // We might need to transform the operand if it is potentially evaluated.
6940 Operand = Actions.HandleExprEvaluationContextForTypeof(Operand.get());
6941 if (Operand.isInvalid()) {
6942 DS.SetTypeSpecError();
6943 return;
6944 }
6945
6946 const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
6947 unsigned DiagID;
6948 // Check for duplicate type specifiers (e.g. "int typeof(int)").
6949 if (DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_typeofExpr, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
6950 DiagID, Operand.get(),
6951 Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy()))
6952 Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
6953}
6954
6955/// [C11] atomic-specifier:
6956/// _Atomic ( type-name )
6957///
6958void Parser::ParseAtomicSpecifier(DeclSpec &DS) {
6959 assert(Tok.is(tok::kw__Atomic) && NextToken().is(tok::l_paren) &&
6960 "Not an atomic specifier");
6961
6962 SourceLocation StartLoc = ConsumeToken();
6963 BalancedDelimiterTracker T(*this, tok::l_paren);
6964 if (T.consumeOpen())
6965 return;
6966
6967 TypeResult Result = ParseTypeName();
6968 if (Result.isInvalid()) {
6969 SkipUntil(tok::r_paren, StopAtSemi);
6970 return;
6971 }
6972
6973 // Match the ')'
6974 T.consumeClose();
6975
6976 if (T.getCloseLocation().isInvalid())
6977 return;
6978
6979 DS.setTypeofParensRange(T.getRange());
6980 DS.SetRangeEnd(T.getCloseLocation());
6981
6982 const char *PrevSpec = nullptr;
6983 unsigned DiagID;
6984 if (DS.SetTypeSpecType(DeclSpec::TST_atomic, StartLoc, PrevSpec,
6985 DiagID, Result.get(),
6986 Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy()))
6987 Diag(StartLoc, DiagID) << PrevSpec;
6988}

6990/// TryAltiVecVectorTokenOutOfLine - Out of line body that should only be called
6991/// from TryAltiVecVectorToken.
6992bool Parser::TryAltiVecVectorTokenOutOfLine() {
6993 Token Next = NextToken();
6994 switch (Next.getKind()) {
6995 default: return false;
6996 case tok::kw_short:
6997 case tok::kw_long:
6998 case tok::kw_signed:
6999 case tok::kw_unsigned:
7000 case tok::kw_void:
7001 case tok::kw_char:
7002 case tok::kw_int:
7003 case tok::kw_float:
7004 case tok::kw_double:
7005 case tok::kw_bool:
7006 case tok::kw___bool:
7007 case tok::kw___pixel:
7008 Tok.setKind(tok::kw___vector);
7009 return true;
7010 case tok::identifier:
7011 if (Next.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_pixel) {
7012 Tok.setKind(tok::kw___vector);
7013 return true;
7014 }
7015 if (Next.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_bool) {
7016 Tok.setKind(tok::kw___vector);
7017 return true;
7018 }
7019 return false;
7020 }
7021}
7022
7023bool Parser::TryAltiVecTokenOutOfLine(DeclSpec &DS, SourceLocation Loc,
7024 const char *&PrevSpec, unsigned &DiagID,
7025 bool &isInvalid) {
7026 const PrintingPolicy &Policy = Actions.getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
7027 if (Tok.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_vector) {
7028 Token Next = NextToken();
7029 switch (Next.getKind()) {
7030 case tok::kw_short:
7031 case tok::kw_long:
7032 case tok::kw_signed:
7033 case tok::kw_unsigned:
7034 case tok::kw_void:
7035 case tok::kw_char:
7036 case tok::kw_int:
7037 case tok::kw_float:
7038 case tok::kw_double:
7039 case tok::kw_bool:
7040 case tok::kw___bool:
7041 case tok::kw___pixel:
7042 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecVector(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
7043 return true;
7044 case tok::identifier:
7045 if (Next.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_pixel) {
7046 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecVector(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,Policy);
7047 return true;
7048 }
7049 if (Next.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_bool) {
7050 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecVector(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID,Policy);
7051 return true;
7052 }
7053 break;
7054 default:
7055 break;
7056 }
7057 } else if ((Tok.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_pixel) &&
7058 DS.isTypeAltiVecVector()) {
7059 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecPixel(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
7060 return true;
7061 } else if ((Tok.getIdentifierInfo() == Ident_bool) &&
7062 DS.isTypeAltiVecVector()) {
7063 isInvalid = DS.SetTypeAltiVecBool(true, Loc, PrevSpec, DiagID, Policy);
7064 return true;
7065 }
7066 return false;
7067}
